  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN382-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai – atu. tuṟai – kaṭainilai. cōḻaṉ nalaṅkiḷḷiyaik kōvūrkiḻār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN382">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>kaṭaṟpaṭai yaṭaṟkoṇṭi</l>
<l>maṇṭuṟṟa malirnōṉṟāṭ</l>
<l>ṭaṇcōḻa nāṭṭupporuna</l>
<l>ṉalaṅkuḷai yaṇiyivuḷi</l>
<l>nalaṅkiḷḷi nacaipporunarēm</l>
<l>piṟarppāṭip peṟalvēṇṭē</l>
<l>mavaṟpāṭutu mavaṉṟāḷ vāḻiyaveṉa</l>
<l>neykuyya vūṉaviṉṟa</l>
<l>palcōṟṟā ṉiṉcuvaiya</l>
<l>nalkuraviṉ pacittuṉpiṉiṉ</l>
<l>muṉṇāḷ viṭṭa mūtaṟi ciṟāarum</l>
<l>yāṉu mēḻmaṇiyaṅ kēḻaṇi yuttik</l>
<l>kaṭkēḷvik kavaināvi</l>
<l>ṉiṟaṉuṟṟa varāappōlum</l>
<l>vaṟaṉorīi vaḻaṅkuvāyppa</l>
<l>viṭumati yattai kaṭumāṉ ṟōṉṟa</l>
<l>ṉiṉatē, munnī ruṭuttaviv viyaṉula kaṟiya</l>
<l>veṉatē, kiṭaikkā ḻaṉṉa teṇkaṇ mākkiṇaik</l>
<l>kaṇṇakat tiyātta nuṇṇaric ciṟukō</l>
<l>leṟitoṟu nuṭaṅki yāṅkuniṉ pakaiñar</l>
<l>kēṭṭoṟu naṭuṅka vēttuveṉ</l>
<l>veṉṟa tērpiṟar vēttavai yāṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>While [we] say: (7d)</l>
<l>“the fighter of the cool Cōḻa land, (3)</l>
<l>with ??? sturdy feet that experienced rushing (2)</l>
<l>for the murderous plunder of the ocean[-like] army, (1)</l>
<l>Nalaṅkiḷḷi, (5a)</l>
<l>[his] horses adorned with swaying manes, (4)</l>
<l>	[his] loving bards we are. (5b)</l>
<l>We don’t need to obtain singing others. (6)</l>
<l>We will sing him. May his foot prosper,”</l>
<l>while [your] giving is excellent (15b)</l>
<l>of things with sweet taste in a lot of rice (10)</l>
<l>that accentuates the meat seasoned with ghee, (9)</l>
<l>	dispelling the drought [with toddy] (15a)</l>
<l>that resembles a snake that hit the very life spot, (14)</l>
<l>with a forked tongue [and] hearing by [its] eyes, (13)</l>
<l>with a head ornament adorned with the lustre of seven gems, (12)</l>
<l>the kids who know [you] of old who had left you on a former day (11)</l>
<l>along with [their] distress of hunger because of poverty (10)</l>
<l>and me, (12k)</l>
<l>leut us go, appearance on a fast horse! (16)</l>
<l>So that this wide world encirlcled by the three-watered [seas] knows of you (17)</l>
<l>I shall praise [you] so that whenever they hear [it] they will tremble, (21)</l>
<l>your enemies, wavering like (20bc)</l>
<l>the Kiṇai drum with a clear eye like ??? of mine (18)</l>
<l>whenever the fine ??? little stick tied to the middle of the eye is beaten, (19-20a)</l>
<l>in the royal assembly of others with victorious chariot. (22)</l>
</lg>
